WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:17.250 --> 00:19.250
[♪ Nat King Cole: "Orange Colored Sky"]

00:24.208 --> 00:26.125
♪ I was walking along ♪

00:26.208 --> 00:28.291
♪ Mindin' my business ♪

00:28.375 --> 00:31.708
♪ When out of an orange-colored sky ♪

00:31.791 --> 00:35.875
♪ Flash, bam, alakazam ♪

00:35.916 --> 00:38.250
♪ Wonderful you came by ♪

00:38.333 --> 00:40.791
♪ I was hummin' a tune ♪

00:40.875 --> 00:43.166
♪ Drinkin' in sunshine ♪

00:43.250 --> 00:46.500
♪ When out of that orange-colored view ♪

00:46.583 --> 00:49.791
♪ Flash, bam, alakazam ♪

00:49.875 --> 00:53.125
♪ I got a look at you ♪

00:53.208 --> 00:56.041
♪ One look and I yelled "timber"...

00:56.125 --> 00:58.750
[newscaster] [over radio] ...negotiations
were scheduled to continue today

00:58.833 --> 01:01.916
as the White House had no comment
about the President's whereabouts.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.500
♪ And the bottom fell out,
I went into a spin ♪

01:03.583 --> 01:05.750
♪ And I started to shout,
"I've been hit..."

01:05.833 --> 01:07.833
[Mr. Handy] Ready to be of service, madam.

01:07.875 --> 01:09.833
[news anchor] ...between
America and her adversaries

01:09.875 --> 01:12.666
crumbled this morning
in Anchorage, Alaska.

01:12.750 --> 01:15.583
The specter of nuclear war
facing this nation

01:15.666 --> 01:17.583
for ten long years is final...

01:17.666 --> 01:19.083
♪ Alakazam...

01:19.166 --> 01:21.666
It's a party, let's just...
focus on the party.

01:21.750 --> 01:23.708
-Okay?
-♪ Purple-striped ♪

01:23.791 --> 01:27.000
♪ Pretty green polka-dot sky ♪

01:27.083 --> 01:31.333
♪ Flash, bam, alakazam ♪

01:31.416 --> 01:33.750
♪ And goodbye ♪♪

01:33.833 --> 01:35.708
[cheering]

01:38.416 --> 01:40.000
All right, birthday boy.

01:40.083 --> 01:42.625
Let's get a photo of you
up here on Sugarfoot.

01:42.708 --> 01:46.541
Why the hell is Cooper Howard
working kids' birthday parties?

01:46.625 --> 01:49.041
-What else? Alimony.
-[chuckles]

01:50.750 --> 01:52.000
What'd they say, Dad?

01:53.708 --> 01:56.666
That I'm lucky to have
such a good helper like you.

01:58.875 --> 02:00.125
All right, you ready?

02:01.541 --> 02:02.625
[shutter clicks]

02:02.708 --> 02:03.708
-It's good.
-All right.

02:03.791 --> 02:06.166
Good. Here we go, bud. [grunts]

02:06.250 --> 02:07.750
Hey, honey. Honey.

02:07.833 --> 02:09.416
Get with Cooper. Let's get a picture.

02:09.500 --> 02:11.375
-Uh, you bet. Yeah.
-[chuckles] Oh, yeah.

02:11.416 --> 02:12.416
[Cooper] All right.

02:12.541 --> 02:14.916
Aw, Coop, Coop, Coop.
Do your thumbs-up.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.500
Yeah, you know,
given the state of everything,

02:17.583 --> 02:19.333
I'd prefer not to, if that's all right.

02:19.416 --> 02:20.666
Why not?

02:20.750 --> 02:21.750
It's what you're famous for.

02:21.833 --> 02:23.208
-Yeah.
-Drop it, Bob.

02:23.291 --> 02:25.875
We gotta... we got to get
this rodeo on the road.

02:25.958 --> 02:27.625
I can't thank you enough, Mr. Howard.

02:27.708 --> 02:29.458
Pleasure's all mine, ma'am.

02:29.541 --> 02:31.291
I hope your son had a lovely birthday.

02:31.375 --> 02:32.791
-Perfect.
-Yeah.

02:32.875 --> 02:34.041
Who's ready for cake?

02:34.125 --> 02:35.833
-[children] Me!
-[Cooper] All right. You ready, Janey?

02:35.916 --> 02:37.916
[children shouting]

02:38.000 --> 02:39.208
[Cooper] Come on. [clicks tongue]

02:39.291 --> 02:40.541
There you go.

02:40.625 --> 02:42.000
-Pinko.
-Yep.

02:42.083 --> 02:43.625
He still took my money.

02:43.708 --> 02:48.583
♪ Happy birthday dear Roy ♪

02:48.666 --> 02:53.416
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪♪

02:53.500 --> 02:55.666
-[whistles]
-[cheering]

03:01.125 --> 03:03.666
...that Los Angeles sunshine
coming through.

03:03.750 --> 03:06.166
Hal, I can't...
I'm sorry, I can't do this.

03:06.250 --> 03:08.750
I can't do the weather
if I don't even know if there's

03:08.833 --> 03:10.750
-gonna be a next week.
-Only thinking happy thoughts today.

03:10.833 --> 03:12.333
[audio shifting]

03:12.416 --> 03:15.541
[announcer] Sugar Bombs presents
Grognak the Barbarian

03:15.625 --> 03:17.916
-and the Ruby Ruins.
-[children laugh, cheer]

03:18.000 --> 03:20.750
[TV show continues indistinctly]

03:23.208 --> 03:25.541
[groans] All right.

03:25.625 --> 03:27.541
[TV playing]

03:27.625 --> 03:29.291
[Cooper] I think that's everything.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.083
[sighs]

03:31.166 --> 03:32.791
Why wouldn't you do it?

03:32.875 --> 03:34.416
The thumbs-up.

03:35.625 --> 03:37.208
Oh, it's, uh...

03:37.291 --> 03:39.166
That's grown-up stuff.

03:44.291 --> 03:45.208
[smacks lips]

03:45.291 --> 03:46.875
Well, back when I was in the Marines,

03:46.958 --> 03:50.375
they taught us that
if they ever drop a really big bomb,

03:50.458 --> 03:53.041
told us to hold up your thumb
just like this.

03:53.125 --> 03:56.791
And if the cloud is smaller
than your thumb,

03:56.875 --> 03:58.625
well, you run for the hills.

03:58.708 --> 04:00.708
And if it's bigger than your thumb?

04:02.458 --> 04:04.291
They told us not to bother running.

04:05.333 --> 04:07.500
Do you think it's gonna happen?

04:08.958 --> 04:11.291
I certainly hope not.

04:11.375 --> 04:14.666
But us cowpokes,
we take it as it comes, right?

04:17.250 --> 04:19.000
[children laughing, chattering]

04:20.875 --> 04:22.541
Can I have a slice, Dad?

04:22.625 --> 04:25.125
You know what? Let me see

04:25.207 --> 04:26.916
if I can't rustle you up a piece.

04:28.332 --> 04:32.041
[TV playing indistinctly]

04:32.125 --> 04:34.375
[laughing]

04:34.457 --> 04:36.291
[door closes]

04:49.207 --> 04:51.041
[Cooper] All right,
one piece of cake coming up

04:51.125 --> 04:53.166
for my favorite cowgirl.

04:53.250 --> 04:55.750
Is it your thumb or mine?

05:01.750 --> 05:04.750
[eerie music playing]

05:10.208 --> 05:12.208
♪ ♪

05:19.750 --> 05:22.582
That's smoke, Janey. It's just a fire.

05:22.666 --> 05:24.666
♪ ♪

05:36.541 --> 05:38.541
[muffled TV playing]

05:38.625 --> 05:41.125
♪ ♪

05:55.416 --> 05:57.582
[rumbling]

05:57.666 --> 06:00.500
[intense music playing]

06:00.583 --> 06:02.583
[muffled shouting]

06:11.666 --> 06:12.916
[muffled] Let us in with you.

06:13.000 --> 06:14.583
[muffled] No room. Back off.

06:16.500 --> 06:18.500
[dramatic music playing]

06:43.082 --> 06:45.791
♪ ♪

07:13.958 --> 07:16.707
[♪ Perry Como:
"Don't Let the Stars Get in Your Eyes"]

07:16.791 --> 07:18.832
My name is Lucy MacLean,

07:18.916 --> 07:22.082
and I'm an active contributor
to the wellbeing of my community.

07:22.166 --> 07:23.791
Repair Skills.

07:23.875 --> 07:27.207
I enjoy participating
in the Young Pipefitter's Association,

07:27.291 --> 07:29.332
which keeps me active.

07:29.416 --> 07:30.750
Science Skills.

07:30.832 --> 07:33.375
Obviously, mine are nothing
compared to my dad's,

07:33.457 --> 07:35.957
but I always relish a challenge.

07:36.041 --> 07:37.916
Speech Skills.

07:38.000 --> 07:40.291
My primary passion is
teaching American History,

07:40.375 --> 07:41.500
with a focus on ethics.

07:41.582 --> 07:44.875
I also participate in Gymnastics Club,

07:44.957 --> 07:46.582
Fencing Team C...

07:48.166 --> 07:50.250
...Intermediate Phys Ed...

07:51.916 --> 07:53.250
...and I dabble in Riflery.

07:54.916 --> 07:56.250
Though I'm not very good.

07:56.332 --> 07:58.207
♪ Change your mind...

07:58.291 --> 07:59.541
In my personal time,

07:59.625 --> 08:01.000
I enjoy taking walks

08:01.083 --> 08:02.958
and watching movies with my dad,

08:03.041 --> 08:04.875
gardening-- also with my dad--

08:04.958 --> 08:07.541
and participating in my family book club.

08:08.375 --> 08:10.916
We're still trying
to get my brother on board.

08:11.000 --> 08:12.833
He'll come around when he's ready.

08:13.833 --> 08:15.791
My reproductive organs are intact,

08:15.875 --> 08:17.207
my hygiene well-maintained,

08:17.291 --> 08:20.207
and yet I have been unable to

08:20.291 --> 08:21.791
find a suitable marriage partner.

08:21.875 --> 08:24.332
At least, one I'm not related to.

08:24.416 --> 08:26.416
And we have rules about that for a reason.

08:26.500 --> 08:27.875
♪ I'll ever love...

08:27.957 --> 08:30.666
So, it is with sound mind and body

08:30.750 --> 08:33.415
that I hereby submit
my application to the council

08:33.500 --> 08:36.415
to participate in
the Triennial Trade with Vault 32.

08:36.540 --> 08:38.332
♪ Don't let the moon break your heart ♪

08:38.415 --> 08:40.415
♪ ♪

08:50.333 --> 08:51.665
[chimes]

08:52.708 --> 08:54.625
♪ You're the only one ♪

08:54.708 --> 08:59.000
♪ You're the only one I'll ever love ♪♪

08:59.083 --> 09:00.083
[sighs happily]

09:03.125 --> 09:05.125
[cheerful music playing]

09:16.333 --> 09:17.666
Norman.

09:17.750 --> 09:18.750
[beeps]

09:23.083 --> 09:24.666
[soft chuckle]

09:42.250 --> 09:44.040
♪ ♪

09:45.540 --> 09:46.708
Hmm.

09:46.790 --> 09:48.165
Feels a little tight.

09:48.250 --> 09:49.625
Won't be for long.

09:49.708 --> 09:53.000
On my wedding night, that dress got off
almost as fast as Burt did.

09:53.083 --> 09:54.125
Huh.

09:55.208 --> 09:56.833
[exhales]

09:56.915 --> 09:59.625
Oh, gosh. After ten years of cousin stuff,

09:59.708 --> 10:01.625
I'm definitely excited
for the real thing.

10:01.708 --> 10:03.666
Oh, Lucy.

10:03.750 --> 10:06.541
I am just excited for us
to raise our kids together.

10:07.583 --> 10:09.000
[soft chuckle]

10:21.041 --> 10:22.500
[chuckles]

10:22.583 --> 10:24.583
[optimistic music playing]

10:36.333 --> 10:37.708
[projector clicking]

10:41.665 --> 10:43.750
[pulsing, intriguing music playing]

10:54.500 --> 10:56.750
[chuckles] Dad.

10:58.833 --> 11:01.875
-My little Sugarbomb.
-Oh. [chuckles]

11:03.833 --> 11:05.416
Oh.

11:05.500 --> 11:08.708
Gosh, you look just like your mother.

11:09.833 --> 11:11.791
Yeah. I wish she was here.

11:11.875 --> 11:13.500
Me, too.

11:13.583 --> 11:16.500
Were you scared?

11:16.583 --> 11:19.166
-When you married Mom?
-Me? [scoffs]

11:19.250 --> 11:20.500
Terrified.

11:20.583 --> 11:22.166
[both laugh]

11:22.250 --> 11:25.375
Well, I'd never stepped foot
outside Vault 31.

11:25.458 --> 11:28.416
When did it go away?

11:28.500 --> 11:31.166
The moment I met your mother.

11:31.250 --> 11:33.500
[inaudible dialogue]

11:33.583 --> 11:35.208
[sentimental music playing]

11:38.458 --> 11:42.125
From that moment on, Vault 31
was a distant memory to me.

11:45.250 --> 11:48.333
Overseer, it's time.

11:49.750 --> 11:51.750
[optimistic music playing]

12:01.875 --> 12:04.000
[door whooshes open]

12:05.375 --> 12:06.958
[door stops]

12:11.708 --> 12:12.875
[Norm] Must be nerve-racking.

12:12.958 --> 12:14.875
Your husband could be anybody.

12:14.958 --> 12:16.125
I'm aware.

12:16.208 --> 12:17.500
-And as for his looks?
-Who knows?

12:17.583 --> 12:18.583
Big butt? No butt?

12:18.666 --> 12:20.125
But, of course,

12:20.208 --> 12:22.000
it's just superficial concerns.
It's what's on the inside that counts.

12:22.083 --> 12:23.208
That's right.

12:23.291 --> 12:25.041
And in that respect,
he could be a cannibal, or just like

12:25.125 --> 12:26.000
crammed full of tumors.

12:26.083 --> 12:27.208
-Norman.
-[door whooshes open]

12:27.291 --> 12:28.125
Sorry, Dad.

12:33.125 --> 12:36.250
[suspenseful music playing]

12:38.583 --> 12:41.208
[rumbling]

12:42.540 --> 12:43.500
[Hank] Gate-Keeper.

12:50.915 --> 12:53.000
-Chet.
-Honestly...

12:53.083 --> 12:54.833
textbook tumbler jam.

12:54.915 --> 12:57.833
It's gonna take some time to fix.

12:57.915 --> 13:00.333
Probably best
if we reschedule with the 32s

13:00.416 --> 13:01.541
-until maintenance and I can...
-Chet.

13:02.375 --> 13:05.250
What's going on?

13:05.333 --> 13:06.833
Lucy, I love you.

13:09.875 --> 13:11.500
We all know that, Chet.

13:11.583 --> 13:13.541
Messing around with your cousin,

13:13.625 --> 13:16.625
it's all well and good for kids,
but it's not a sustainable,

13:16.708 --> 13:18.791
long-term sexual practice, you know?

13:20.416 --> 13:21.833
Yeah, I know.

13:30.750 --> 13:32.040
[alarm buzzing]

14:01.333 --> 14:04.250
Welcome, neighbors from Vault 32.

14:04.333 --> 14:06.250
I am Hank MacLean,

14:06.333 --> 14:08.375
overseer of Vault 33.

14:08.458 --> 14:11.625
Lee Moldaver, overseer of 32.

14:13.125 --> 14:15.041
Thank you for your hospitality.

14:15.125 --> 14:18.083
Oh, we were sorry to hear
of Overseer Jackson's passing

14:18.166 --> 14:19.500
in your telegrams.

14:19.583 --> 14:22.250
When blight hit our wheat,

14:22.333 --> 14:24.500
we lost a lot of good people,
but this trade

14:24.583 --> 14:26.875
will help us get back on our feet.

14:26.958 --> 14:30.958
Yes, well, as arranged,
we offer you seed and parts

14:31.041 --> 14:34.125
-for machinery.
-In exchange, we offer you a breeder.

14:34.208 --> 14:37.125
So... [chuckles]

14:37.208 --> 14:39.333
who am I marrying? [chuckles]

14:39.415 --> 14:41.415
[tense music playing]

14:50.833 --> 14:51.833
I'm Lucy.

14:51.915 --> 14:54.500
Do you have a name?

14:54.583 --> 14:55.790
Monty.

15:01.458 --> 15:03.083
Lucky.

15:03.166 --> 15:05.000
