21:15.791 --> 21:17.125
[wipes]

21:17.208 --> 21:19.125
♪ Though I adored ♪

21:19.208 --> 21:22.041
♪ The times before ♪

21:22.125 --> 21:25.666
♪ They never felt like this ♪♪

21:25.750 --> 21:27.750
[ominous music playing]

21:50.875 --> 21:52.916
Hello?

22:03.083 --> 22:05.958
[faint booming in distance]

22:06.958 --> 22:08.458
[grunts]

22:08.541 --> 22:10.958
[faucet running]

22:14.208 --> 22:15.833
[distant yelling]

22:15.916 --> 22:17.541
[suspenseful music playing]

22:33.666 --> 22:35.708
[woman screams in distance]

22:35.791 --> 22:37.250
[dramatic music playing]

22:37.333 --> 22:40.000
[peaking]

22:44.041 --> 22:46.375
[Lucy] You're from the surface.

22:52.791 --> 22:54.541
Raiders.

22:54.625 --> 22:55.875
[intense music playing]

22:55.958 --> 22:58.166
[grunting]

23:10.666 --> 23:11.791
[screams]

23:11.875 --> 23:13.750
-Ah...
-[high-pitched ringing]

23:13.833 --> 23:16.458
[muffled groaning]

23:24.833 --> 23:26.791
[Lucy panting]

23:26.875 --> 23:28.708
[Monty] Just so you know...

23:30.291 --> 23:32.500
...this was the best day of my life.

23:36.166 --> 23:37.250
[grunts]

23:39.375 --> 23:40.375
[screams]

23:53.958 --> 23:55.083
[knife slashes]

23:56.291 --> 23:57.541
[screams]

23:58.458 --> 23:59.875
[knife pierces flesh]

23:59.958 --> 24:01.250
[Lucy panting]

24:23.458 --> 24:25.958
[alarm blaring]

24:28.083 --> 24:29.458
[gurgles]

24:32.083 --> 24:34.916
[panting]

24:40.375 --> 24:42.500
[yells]

24:44.583 --> 24:47.333
[labored breathing]

24:47.416 --> 24:49.375
[dramatic music playing]

25:00.708 --> 25:02.041
[hissing]

25:02.125 --> 25:03.708
[grunts]

25:07.791 --> 25:10.791
[alarm continues blaring]

25:35.583 --> 25:36.791
[gasps]

25:49.125 --> 25:51.083
♪ ♪

26:04.000 --> 26:06.625
♪ ♪

26:16.750 --> 26:20.958
-[♪ The Castells:
"Some Enchanted Evening"]
-♪ Who can explain it? ♪

26:21.041 --> 26:24.541
♪ Who can tell you why? ♪

26:24.625 --> 26:29.250
♪ Fools give you reasons ♪

26:29.333 --> 26:32.333
♪ Wise men never ♪

26:32.416 --> 26:35.791
♪ Try ♪

26:37.458 --> 26:41.500
♪ Some enchanted evening ♪

26:41.583 --> 26:45.083
♪ Some enchanted
evening ♪

26:45.166 --> 26:49.041
-♪ When you find your true love ♪
-[yelling]

26:50.916 --> 26:54.625
♪ When you feel her call you ♪

26:54.708 --> 26:58.750
♪ Whoa, across ♪

26:58.833 --> 27:03.333
♪ A crowded room ♪

27:03.416 --> 27:05.958
♪ Then fly to her side ♪

27:06.041 --> 27:08.083
♪ Then fly...

27:08.166 --> 27:10.541
Get that jelly mold out of here!

27:10.625 --> 27:13.833
♪ And make her your own ♪

27:16.541 --> 27:18.875
♪ Or all through your life ♪

27:18.958 --> 27:24.166
♪ You may dream ♪

27:24.250 --> 27:27.083
♪ All alone ♪

27:29.625 --> 27:33.125
♪ Some enchanted evening ♪

27:33.208 --> 27:36.375
♪ Some enchanted
evening ♪

27:36.458 --> 27:39.958
♪ You may see a stranger ♪

27:40.041 --> 27:41.541
[gasps]

27:42.791 --> 27:48.000
♪ You may see a stranger ♪

27:48.083 --> 27:49.916
♪ Across ♪

27:50.000 --> 27:54.166
♪ A crowded room ♪

27:55.166 --> 27:57.833
♪ And somehow you know ♪

27:57.916 --> 28:01.625
♪ And somehow
you know ♪

28:01.708 --> 28:03.291
♪ You know ♪

28:03.375 --> 28:07.000
-♪ Even then ♪
-[screaming]

28:07.083 --> 28:09.791
♪ That somewhere ♪

28:09.875 --> 28:13.041
♪ You'll see her ♪

28:13.125 --> 28:18.958
♪ Again and again...

28:19.041 --> 28:20.291
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Easy, pal.

28:20.375 --> 28:21.583
[grunts]

28:22.916 --> 28:25.333
Sir, please don't make me use force.

28:26.416 --> 28:27.500
[hissing]

28:27.583 --> 28:30.083
Oh, geez.

28:30.166 --> 28:31.291
[grunting]

28:35.583 --> 28:39.208
♪ Some enchanted evening ♪

28:39.291 --> 28:42.166
♪ Some enchanted
evening ♪

28:42.250 --> 28:47.125
♪ When you find your true love ♪♪

28:47.208 --> 28:49.708
[dark music playing]

28:56.833 --> 28:58.291
[yells]

29:24.833 --> 29:26.791
♪ ♪

29:55.125 --> 29:57.458
♪ ♪

30:25.666 --> 30:27.625
♪ ♪

30:40.000 --> 30:42.625
[steady beeping]

30:55.458 --> 30:57.416
[panting]

30:58.625 --> 31:00.375
[Moldaver] Welcome.

31:02.708 --> 31:04.666
[suspenseful music playing]

31:06.125 --> 31:07.375
Oh.

31:08.916 --> 31:10.833
I think I know who you are.

31:10.916 --> 31:13.833
Everyone knows who I am.

31:16.666 --> 31:18.875
But do they know who they are?

31:20.875 --> 31:22.708
They are the product

31:22.791 --> 31:26.541
of one of life's tricky little choices.

31:29.916 --> 31:31.583
So I'm gonna offer you a choice.

31:33.500 --> 31:35.041
Them or her.

31:35.125 --> 31:36.875
[somber music playing]

31:43.208 --> 31:45.500
[beeping]

31:59.875 --> 32:01.000
[Lucy] Hey.

32:01.083 --> 32:02.500
H-Hey, stop.

32:02.583 --> 32:04.166
-Dad. Wait.
-Lucy, please.

32:04.250 --> 32:05.916
We have to--

32:06.000 --> 32:07.958
-No. Stop.
-[door locks]

32:09.958 --> 32:12.166
You are my world.

32:25.583 --> 32:29.125
-Dad. Dad! Dad!
-[pounding on door]

32:30.125 --> 32:32.333
Stop! Stop it! Dad!

32:39.041 --> 32:40.916
You look like your mother.

32:46.083 --> 32:47.708
Where are you taking him?

32:48.708 --> 32:50.458
To the real world.

32:50.541 --> 32:52.416
You should see it sometime.

32:52.500 --> 32:54.416
[dramatic music playing]

32:55.500 --> 32:56.708
No, wait.

32:56.791 --> 32:58.291
Stop!

33:02.750 --> 33:05.291
Stop! Stop!

33:05.375 --> 33:07.208
Maybe you should do what you do best.

33:07.291 --> 33:09.875
-Stop!
-Run and hide.

33:10.958 --> 33:12.291
[beeps]

33:15.166 --> 33:17.625
[panting]

33:23.583 --> 33:25.583
[rapid beeping]

33:41.000 --> 33:43.083
[wind whooshing]

33:47.875 --> 33:50.291
[♪ Johnny Cash: "So Doggone Lonesome"]

33:51.000 --> 33:52.250
♪ I do my best to hide...

33:52.333 --> 33:54.541
-[all shouting]
-Hit him again.

33:54.625 --> 33:56.541
♪ I try to make believe ♪

33:56.625 --> 33:58.250
♪ There's nothing wrong...

33:58.333 --> 34:00.875
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

34:00.958 --> 34:03.333
Kickin' your ass. You like that, huh?

34:04.500 --> 34:06.250
[grunts]

34:06.333 --> 34:07.541
♪ That you're gone ♪♪

34:09.625 --> 34:11.625
Yo, let's go, let's go.

34:21.125 --> 34:23.416
[panting]

34:23.500 --> 34:25.041
[Dane] Hey. [grunts]

34:26.500 --> 34:28.250
How's your nose?

34:28.333 --> 34:29.875
[grunts]

34:29.958 --> 34:32.000
I can still smell, it's just...

34:32.083 --> 34:34.625
mostly blood.

34:36.333 --> 34:38.208
Flesh is weak, but steel endures.

34:38.291 --> 34:40.375
I-I know.

34:40.458 --> 34:42.583
[song resumes]

34:43.583 --> 34:45.375
-Come on.
-Yeah.

34:45.458 --> 34:47.833
Uh-huh. [grunts]

34:47.916 --> 34:49.250
Yeah.

34:52.708 --> 34:56.083
♪ If they ask me, I guess I'd be denying ♪

34:57.125 --> 34:59.875
♪ That I've been unhappy all alone ♪

35:01.125 --> 35:04.791
♪ But if they heard my heart,
they'd hear it crying ♪

35:05.833 --> 35:09.166
♪ "Where's my darling,
when's she coming home?" ♪♪

35:09.250 --> 35:11.291
[Felix] It is the duty
of the Brotherhood of Steel

35:11.375 --> 35:13.208
to secure the Wasteland.

35:13.291 --> 35:16.083
One day as squires, you will help knights

35:16.166 --> 35:20.083
find and identify prewar tech.

35:20.166 --> 35:23.000
Aspirant Maximus.

35:27.833 --> 35:30.875
Can you identify this relic?

35:32.625 --> 35:34.500
It's a... [clears throat]

35:34.583 --> 35:36.208
...rotor?

35:36.291 --> 35:37.708
[grunts]

35:37.791 --> 35:39.583
[Felix] A circuit.

35:39.666 --> 35:42.875
The ability to defend yourself
is but one part of your training.

35:42.958 --> 35:48.625
We are the finders and the preservers.

35:48.708 --> 35:51.375
Unless you know what to find and preserve,

35:51.458 --> 35:56.208
you are more useful as a corpse.

35:58.791 --> 36:00.625
[whirring]

36:03.541 --> 36:05.500
[atmospheric music playing]

36:07.041 --> 36:09.916
[quiet murmuring]

36:25.916 --> 36:27.875
♪ ♪

36:39.291 --> 36:40.750
Yeah, look at that shit.

36:40.833 --> 36:42.750
[dramatic music playing]

36:46.666 --> 36:49.708
-[aspirant] What kind of model is that?
-It's the T-60.

36:49.791 --> 36:52.041
Imagine getting to put on
one of those every day.

36:59.625 --> 37:01.916
Wonder why they're here.

37:03.916 --> 37:05.916
[officer] [over radio] A-17.

37:08.333 --> 37:10.291
A-20.

37:12.083 --> 37:13.708
B-11.

37:15.708 --> 37:18.125
N-24.

37:29.750 --> 37:31.000
[grunts]

37:31.083 --> 37:33.833
[insects buzzing]

37:35.291 --> 37:36.500
Come on, I got something
I want to show you.

37:36.583 --> 37:38.125
Latrine duty's a two-person job.

37:38.208 --> 37:40.625
[sighs] I said come on.

37:40.708 --> 37:42.750
That hole of shit isn't going anywhere.

37:48.208 --> 37:49.833
[laughs softly]

37:52.666 --> 37:54.958
[cans chiming]

37:55.041 --> 37:56.958
[atmospheric music]

38:24.250 --> 38:26.208
♪ ♪

38:42.041 --> 38:43.625
[Shortsight] Aspirant Dane?

38:45.625 --> 38:48.458
-Th-This was my idea. He didn't want--
-You're being summoned. Come with me.

38:51.541 --> 38:54.500
[somber music playing]

38:57.250 --> 38:59.208
[♪ Johnny Cash: "All Over Again"]

39:02.333 --> 39:06.541
♪ Every time I look at you,
I fall in love ♪

39:07.583 --> 39:10.166
♪ All over again ♪

39:11.250 --> 39:13.125
-[grunting]
-♪ Every time I think of you ♪

39:13.208 --> 39:15.291
♪ It all begins ♪

39:16.583 --> 39:19.166
♪ All over again...

39:19.250 --> 39:21.291
[whooping in distance]

39:21.375 --> 39:23.375
-[cheering]
-[applause]

39:40.458 --> 39:41.708
What's going on?

39:43.125 --> 39:45.416
A bunch of us were chosen to get anointed.

39:45.500 --> 39:46.958
[Thaddeus] Hey.

39:47.041 --> 39:49.250
-What's your title gonna be?
-Squire. To Knight Titus.

39:49.333 --> 39:51.250
And get this, we're going to the Wilds.

39:51.333 --> 39:52.791
-[cheering]
-Hell yeah, you are!

39:52.875 --> 39:53.875
[Maximus] Dane...

39:53.958 --> 39:55.250
[others] [chanting] Dane! Dane! Dane!

39:55.333 --> 39:57.500
Dane! Dane! Dane! Dane!

39:57.583 --> 40:00.458
Dane! Dane! Dane! Dane! Dane! Dane!

40:00.541 --> 40:02.500
[cheering]

40:02.583 --> 40:04.833
[laughter]

40:04.916 --> 40:07.625
[indistinct chatter]

40:12.083 --> 40:14.083
-[aspirant 1] Hey, you're next,
you're next.
-[aspirant 2] Yeah.

40:17.416 --> 40:21.000
[haunting music playing]

40:21.083 --> 40:23.500
[grunting]

40:25.583 --> 40:28.750
[shouting]

40:38.416 --> 40:40.666
[laughter in distance]

40:49.791 --> 40:52.375
[Dane screaming]

41:01.250 --> 41:02.791
What happened?

41:02.875 --> 41:04.791
[Dane panting]

41:07.041 --> 41:08.125
Give me that.

41:15.875 --> 41:17.833
[intense, ominous music playing]

41:28.750 --> 41:30.750
[♪ Connie Conway: "Brighter Side"]

41:37.041 --> 41:41.375
♪ There's a brighter side ♪

41:41.458 --> 41:46.041
♪ To every dark, dark cloud ♪

41:46.125 --> 41:50.958
♪ And there's a smiling face ♪

41:51.041 --> 41:53.208
♪ In every crowd ♪

41:53.291 --> 41:54.958
[groaning]

41:57.583 --> 42:04.500
♪ All your troubles will soon fade away ♪

42:04.583 --> 42:07.625
♪ There's a brighter ♪

42:07.708 --> 42:10.375
♪ Brighter ♪

42:10.458 --> 42:15.083
♪ Side ♪♪

42:15.166 --> 42:17.541
[indistinct chatter]

42:17.625 --> 42:19.000
[Reg] Everyone settle.

42:22.250 --> 42:25.208
I have a proposal for the assembly.

42:30.333 --> 42:33.041
We send a search party
to the surface to find my dad.

42:33.125 --> 42:34.291
-[grumbling]
-[man] To the surface?

42:34.375 --> 42:35.791
[Lucy] We can spare
four people from farm duty

42:35.875 --> 42:37.291
for up to two weeks,

42:37.375 --> 42:38.583
even with our dwindled numbers.

42:38.666 --> 42:41.000
Sorry, Lucy, but you're talking about

42:41.083 --> 42:43.166
opening the outer vault door?

42:43.250 --> 42:44.916
Just for under a minute.

42:45.000 --> 42:46.791
Okay? It's just enough time to--

42:46.875 --> 42:49.250
Okay, I-I know we're just...
we're brainstorming here,

42:49.333 --> 42:51.208
and there's no bad ideas
in a brainstorm...

42:51.291 --> 42:52.750
-[man] Maybe for you.
-...but that's not something

42:52.833 --> 42:53.916
that we ever do

42:54.000 --> 42:55.875
or have ever done, never, ever, ever.

42:55.958 --> 42:57.041
I-I know, I know that.

42:57.125 --> 43:00.541
I know we're all hurting right now,

43:00.625 --> 43:02.166
but our first priority

43:02.250 --> 43:05.916
has to be to maintain
the security of this vault.

43:06.000 --> 43:08.791
That means not opening any of our doors.

43:08.875 --> 43:09.958
Well said, Betty.

43:10.041 --> 43:11.791
[Woody] Yes, thank you, Betty.

43:11.875 --> 43:13.083
Okay, let's move on.

43:13.166 --> 43:15.166
[Norm] They don't want to find Dad.

43:16.916 --> 43:19.375
If they did, they wouldn't
get to be in charge.

43:19.458 --> 43:22.333
[quiet, dramatic music playing]

43:43.541 --> 43:44.958
[sighs]

43:50.583 --> 43:51.875
♪ ♪

43:57.958 --> 43:59.958
[pulsing, dramatic music playing]

44:16.875 --> 44:18.208
Hey, Davey.

44:18.291 --> 44:19.500
-Hey.
-How's your day going?

44:20.500 --> 44:22.458
Bad as everyone else's.

44:26.875 --> 44:28.208
[groans]

44:28.291 --> 44:30.458
[mutters]

44:42.416 --> 44:43.666
[horn blares]

44:47.375 --> 44:49.375
[horn blares]

44:51.750 --> 44:53.458
[horn blares]

44:53.541 --> 44:55.541
[dramatic, ethereal music playing]

45:12.750 --> 45:13.916
[Lucy] Hold the elevator.

45:20.583 --> 45:22.916
♪ ♪

45:28.291 --> 45:29.291
Take care of Norm

45:29.375 --> 45:31.166
till I'm back, okay?

45:32.708 --> 45:34.625
I can't.

45:34.708 --> 45:36.875
I'm going with you.

45:36.958 --> 45:39.041
-Chet--
-What you're doing is insane.

45:39.125 --> 45:40.791
You don't even know which way to go.

45:40.875 --> 45:42.750
It isn't like the vault out there.

45:42.833 --> 45:43.791
It's big.

45:44.791 --> 45:46.500
[horn blares]

45:49.416 --> 45:50.833
Chet...

45:50.916 --> 45:52.750
I'm not letting anyone else

45:52.833 --> 45:54.291
get hurt on my behalf.

45:54.375 --> 45:55.916
Okay?

45:59.416 --> 46:01.208
♪ ♪

46:01.291 --> 46:02.875
Oh, Lucy.

46:04.833 --> 46:06.958
Oh, okay. There we go.

46:10.458 --> 46:11.958
[exclaims]

46:16.333 --> 46:18.875
I just tranq'd him.

46:18.958 --> 46:20.875
And I'll do the same to you
if you try to follow me.

46:22.291 --> 46:23.500
I'm too chicken.

46:23.583 --> 46:24.875
Thanks.

46:24.958 --> 46:26.875
[emotional music playing]

46:41.916 --> 46:43.583
[horn blares]

46:44.625 --> 46:46.583
[pulsing, dramatic music playing]

46:48.125 --> 46:50.083
[exhales]

46:56.166 --> 46:57.916
I'm bringing him home.

46:58.000 --> 46:59.458
[horn blares]

46:59.541 --> 47:01.750
[whirring]

47:01.833 --> 47:03.958
[horn blares]

47:05.750 --> 47:07.791
[horn blares]

47:23.416 --> 47:25.458
♪ ♪

47:33.875 --> 47:35.083
Stop!

47:35.166 --> 47:36.500
Lucy!

47:36.583 --> 47:38.875
Are you mad?

47:38.958 --> 47:41.666
Young lady, come back here right away!

47:43.291 --> 47:44.791
[Reg] Lucy!

47:46.916 --> 47:48.750
Lucy, no!

47:55.541 --> 47:57.375
-That didn't work.
-[horn blares]

48:01.041 --> 48:03.125
[tense percussive music playing]

48:14.083 --> 48:16.083
[door clanking]

48:19.291 --> 48:20.791
[gasps]

48:24.250 --> 48:25.916
[rad meter peaking]

48:28.833 --> 48:30.833
[ominous, eerie music playing]

49:00.916 --> 49:02.875
♪ ♪

49:15.708 --> 49:17.708
[waves crashing]

49:25.791 --> 49:27.791
[uplifting music playing]

49:46.583 --> 49:48.833
Okey dokey.

49:48.916 --> 49:50.500
[exhales]

50:02.875 --> 50:04.416
[gasps]

50:17.000 --> 50:19.041
[door closes]

50:19.125 --> 50:22.125
We have given you a name.

50:25.041 --> 50:26.333
Food.

50:26.416 --> 50:28.458
Education.

50:28.541 --> 50:30.500
A place in the world.

50:30.583 --> 50:32.500
So...

50:33.625 --> 50:35.958
…we expect you to give us

50:36.041 --> 50:38.541
the truth.

50:38.625 --> 50:40.708
Why did you join the Brotherhood?

50:41.916 --> 50:44.375
To hurt the people who hurt me.

50:44.458 --> 50:47.208
[mysterious music playing]

50:54.041 --> 50:57.291
I understand you're
a friend of Aspirant Dane.

50:57.375 --> 50:59.375
Yes.

50:59.458 --> 51:01.333
You're aware of their injury?

51:01.416 --> 51:02.583
Yes.

51:02.666 --> 51:05.083
Do you know who did it?

51:07.708 --> 51:09.708
No.

51:13.791 --> 51:16.458
Your fellow aspirants say it was you.

51:19.958 --> 51:22.458
No, I… [stammering]

51:22.541 --> 51:24.291
I-I wouldn't...

51:24.375 --> 51:26.083
Why not?

51:26.166 --> 51:28.166
Your friend was promoted, you were not.

51:28.250 --> 51:30.541
You have ambitions, don't you?

51:34.208 --> 51:36.208
[suspenseful music playing]

51:44.625 --> 51:45.750
[knight] Speak.

51:45.833 --> 51:47.750
[stammers] I didn't.

51:47.833 --> 51:50.083
I didn't do it. I did not. I...

51:58.833 --> 52:01.875
[stammers] I wanted it to happen.
Is that wrong?

52:07.083 --> 52:09.250
Yes.

52:09.333 --> 52:10.958
[chuckles]

52:11.041 --> 52:13.041
Yes.

52:13.125 --> 52:14.875
Violence...

52:14.958 --> 52:16.708
is merely a tool.

52:16.791 --> 52:20.666
We use it to bring order
to the Wasteland, but

52:20.750 --> 52:25.416
violence against a Brother of Steel

52:25.500 --> 52:27.791
is a sign of weakness.

52:31.250 --> 52:33.291
But are you?

52:35.500 --> 52:37.875
Weak?

52:41.375 --> 52:44.750
[stammers] I don't want to be. I...

53:02.916 --> 53:04.750
You have anything else to say

53:04.833 --> 53:07.208
in your defense?

53:19.041 --> 53:21.375
I just...

53:23.000 --> 53:25.166
I just...

53:25.250 --> 53:27.625
I-I want to thank you.

53:32.833 --> 53:35.000
[stammers]

53:35.083 --> 53:37.500
For your guidance and...

53:37.583 --> 53:39.416
for giving me a home.

53:39.500 --> 53:42.166
I-I had no place in the world.

53:42.250 --> 53:44.250
So...

53:47.666 --> 53:50.958
…if I can help
the Brotherhood make it better...

53:53.416 --> 53:56.125
...Eden or whatever...

53:58.541 --> 54:01.083
...even if it means giving my own life...

54:02.416 --> 54:04.416
...I'll do it.

54:10.333 --> 54:12.458
[heavy thudding]

54:12.541 --> 54:16.416
And I'd be grateful to the Brotherhood
for giving my life meaning.

54:20.166 --> 54:22.416
Good boy.

54:25.791 --> 54:28.666
Then you will be Knight Titus'

54:28.750 --> 54:30.666
new squire.

54:42.666 --> 54:44.666
[breathing shakily]

54:45.833 --> 54:47.833
[suspenseful music playing]

54:53.458 --> 54:55.458
[man coughing]

55:01.166 --> 55:03.291
It's not so bad.

55:03.375 --> 55:06.416
At least here no one steals your rations.

55:07.625 --> 55:09.666
They said I'll still have
a place at the Brotherhood.

55:11.166 --> 55:13.166
But I heard you got my spot.

55:19.083 --> 55:21.166
You know who did it?

55:21.250 --> 55:22.916
[sputters]

55:23.000 --> 55:25.041
Oh, I've narrowed it down
to any one of those assholes.

55:25.125 --> 55:25.958
[laughter]

55:26.041 --> 55:27.375
-[Thaddeus] Yeah.
-[aspirant] You like that?

55:27.458 --> 55:28.583
-No!
-There you are.

55:28.666 --> 55:30.958
-Ah! Yeah!
-Stop it!

55:31.041 --> 55:32.375
[aspirant] He likes it.

55:32.458 --> 55:34.500
They asked if it was you.

55:41.583 --> 55:43.625
Yeah, they asked me the same thing.

55:46.375 --> 55:48.750
I told 'em you wouldn't hurt a fly.

55:54.208 --> 55:56.541
[intriguing music playing]

56:02.500 --> 56:04.750
[Felix] Aspirant Maximus.

56:04.833 --> 56:08.625
It is your most sacred duty
to protect the Brotherhood.

56:09.666 --> 56:14.083
After which, it is your most sacred duty
to protect the mission.

56:14.166 --> 56:18.291
After which, it is your most sacred duty

56:18.375 --> 56:21.875
to protect your lord Knight Titus.

56:25.041 --> 56:27.958
Do you accept?

56:28.041 --> 56:30.291
♪ ♪

56:51.166 --> 56:55.833
Our mission comes from the highest clerics

56:55.916 --> 56:59.166
in the Commonwealth.

56:59.250 --> 57:01.375
It is believed

57:01.458 --> 57:03.125
that a denizen

57:03.208 --> 57:05.041
of the Enclave

57:05.125 --> 57:06.666
has escaped.

57:06.750 --> 57:08.833
[quietly] The Enclave's real?

57:08.916 --> 57:11.500
And that he has with him an object...

57:12.541 --> 57:15.583
...of profound potential...

57:16.916 --> 57:19.750
...to harm our nation

57:19.833 --> 57:21.583
or to save it.

57:22.583 --> 57:26.666
Each knight in this legion

57:26.750 --> 57:31.500
will search a section of the Wilds
for this target.

57:31.583 --> 57:33.250
Brothers...

57:33.333 --> 57:35.750
-[grunting]
-...we exist

57:35.833 --> 57:38.166
for moments such as these.

57:38.250 --> 57:41.208
Go forth

57:41.291 --> 57:43.333
with honor!

57:44.583 --> 57:46.875
And may the shape of the future

57:46.958 --> 57:49.250
be cut by your sword!

57:49.333 --> 57:50.958
[cheering]

57:51.041 --> 57:53.791
Approximation of the target for your lord.

58:02.541 --> 58:05.375
You're dismissed, Aspirant.

58:08.375 --> 58:11.291
[dramatic music playing]

58:17.208 --> 58:20.041
[whirring]

58:36.458 --> 58:38.583
[indistinct radio transmission]

59:02.666 --> 59:04.750
♪ ♪

59:24.250 --> 59:26.000
-[gunfire in distance]
-[lively music playing]

59:26.083 --> 59:28.083
[cheering]

59:32.791 --> 59:33.791
[weapon launches]

59:33.875 --> 59:35.875
[groaning]

59:37.750 --> 59:38.916
[groans]

59:39.000 --> 59:40.458
[thud]

59:45.125 --> 59:46.583
[tense music playing]

59:46.666 --> 59:48.583
[Slim] How do we know which grave?

59:48.666 --> 59:50.916
[Honcho] Well, Slim,
we look for the fresh one.

59:55.791 --> 59:58.625
Dom Pedro has our friend
dug up once a year.

59:58.708 --> 01:00:03.083
Cuts some pieces off
and puts him right back in the ground.

01:00:10.625 --> 01:00:12.875
Bingo.

01:00:12.958 --> 01:00:14.041
Shit.

01:00:14.125 --> 01:00:17.416
You're telling me
this supreme badass we're looking for

01:00:17.500 --> 01:00:18.958
is a godforsaken mutant?

01:00:19.041 --> 01:00:21.625
Have some respec'.

01:00:21.708 --> 01:00:24.791
That's your prospective coworker
you's talking about

01:00:24.875 --> 01:00:27.250
and our ticket to a big payoff.

01:00:27.333 --> 01:00:28.750
Thought you said you knew this guy.

01:00:28.833 --> 01:00:30.708
I said I knew of him.

01:00:31.708 --> 01:00:33.583
My pop worked with him once.

01:00:33.666 --> 01:00:35.083
Your pop?

01:00:35.166 --> 01:00:37.083
How long's this asshole
been moldering in the ground?

01:00:37.166 --> 01:00:38.458
How do we know he's not feral?

01:00:38.541 --> 01:00:40.416
That is why

01:00:40.500 --> 01:00:42.083
-we brought...
-[clucking]

01:00:42.166 --> 01:00:43.791
...our little friend.

01:00:43.875 --> 01:00:47.166
A feral ghoul can't abide a chicken.

01:00:48.333 --> 01:00:51.166
If he goes for her, we kill him.

01:00:51.250 --> 01:00:53.541
[tense music playing]

01:00:53.625 --> 01:00:55.625
[clucking]

01:00:57.625 --> 01:00:59.625
[grunting]

01:01:02.041 --> 01:01:04.041
[groaning]

01:01:04.125 --> 01:01:06.000
-Whoa, whoa.
-[panting]

01:01:06.083 --> 01:01:08.041
[grunting]

01:01:12.166 --> 01:01:13.791
[jangling]

01:01:14.833 --> 01:01:16.958
[creaking]

01:01:30.708 --> 01:01:32.708
[coyote howls in distance]

01:01:34.291 --> 01:01:36.291
[eerie music playing]

01:01:37.916 --> 01:01:39.916
[breathing heavily]

01:01:41.916 --> 01:01:43.916
[leather creaking]

01:01:49.208 --> 01:01:50.541
[grunts, gasps]

01:01:50.625 --> 01:01:52.000
[shuddering]

01:01:52.083 --> 01:01:54.083
[coughing]

01:01:57.375 --> 01:01:58.750
[hawks, spits]

01:01:58.833 --> 01:02:01.666
[groaning]

01:02:04.708 --> 01:02:07.666
-[cracking]
-[groaning]

01:02:08.875 --> 01:02:10.875
[vocalist yodeling]

01:02:16.208 --> 01:02:18.208
[tense music playing]

01:02:26.958 --> 01:02:27.958
Ah.

01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:36.041
Well, well, well.

01:02:36.125 --> 01:02:39.583
Why, is this an Amish production
of The Count of Monte Cristo or...

01:02:39.666 --> 01:02:43.833
just the weirdest circle jerk
I've ever been invited to?

01:02:46.708 --> 01:02:48.708
[laughing]

01:02:52.583 --> 01:02:54.416
Welcome back.

01:02:54.500 --> 01:02:55.541
I'm Honcho.

01:02:55.625 --> 01:02:56.875
Now, you don't even know us--

01:02:56.958 --> 01:02:58.375
No.

01:02:58.458 --> 01:03:00.125
I do not.

01:03:00.208 --> 01:03:01.541
[clucking]

01:03:13.041 --> 01:03:14.916
Does that count?

01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:17.291
Sh-Should I shoot him?

01:03:17.375 --> 01:03:19.833
Would you shut the fuck up?

01:03:19.916 --> 01:03:21.166
We, uh...

01:03:21.250 --> 01:03:23.458
we got a proposition for you.

01:03:23.541 --> 01:03:25.291
A bounty came down.

01:03:25.375 --> 01:03:26.958
A huge one.

01:03:27.041 --> 01:03:28.541
Enough to be a...

01:03:28.625 --> 01:03:31.541
last score for me and whoever's with me.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:36.166
Yeah. Now, somebody made a run...

01:03:37.750 --> 01:03:39.291
...from the Enclave.

01:03:40.375 --> 01:03:43.208
Well, what makes you think
I'd give a good goddamn about that?

01:03:43.291 --> 01:03:47.208
It ain't where they's running from
I figured you'd be interested in.

01:03:47.291 --> 01:03:48.666
It's where they's running to.

01:03:49.833 --> 01:03:52.666
That witch Moldaver.

01:03:53.833 --> 01:03:55.666
In California.

01:03:56.916 --> 01:03:58.666
That's where you from, ain't it?

01:04:00.083 --> 01:04:01.875
Originally, I mean.

01:04:01.958 --> 01:04:03.916
[vocalist yodeling]

01:04:07.541 --> 01:04:10.375
Now, what the fuck would you know
about where I'm from?

01:04:13.166 --> 01:04:16.708
Well, that don't sound
like gratitude, do it, boys?

01:04:18.083 --> 01:04:20.166
How about we put you
right back in that hole

01:04:20.250 --> 01:04:24.166
so Dom Pedro can have his fun with you
for the next 30 years?

01:04:24.250 --> 01:04:26.708
[tense music playing]

01:04:26.791 --> 01:04:28.791
[breathing heavily]

01:04:33.125 --> 01:04:35.500
Well, I tell you what, boys,

01:04:35.583 --> 01:04:37.916
whenever somebody says...

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:42.666
...they're doing one last job, that
usually means their heart's not in it.

01:04:42.750 --> 01:04:44.666
Probably never was.

01:04:46.916 --> 01:04:48.416
But for me,

01:04:48.500 --> 01:04:50.666
well...

01:04:50.750 --> 01:04:53.041
I do this shit for the love of the game.

01:04:53.125 --> 01:04:54.583
[dramatic music playing]

01:04:54.666 --> 01:04:56.708
[grunting]

01:04:59.125 --> 01:05:01.125
[whimpers]

01:05:01.208 --> 01:05:03.125
[gasping]

01:05:08.083 --> 01:05:10.458
[ominous music playing]

01:05:31.458 --> 01:05:33.333
[Ghoul] You right, friend,
about one thing.

01:05:36.291 --> 01:05:37.833
This right here

01:05:37.916 --> 01:05:40.750
was your last job.

01:05:40.833 --> 01:05:43.541
My paycheck wasn't quite
what you expected, but...

01:05:43.625 --> 01:05:45.916
well, you know what they say.

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:47.916
Us cowpokes...

01:05:50.666 --> 01:05:52.375
[grunting]

01:05:53.708 --> 01:05:55.041
[thud]

01:05:55.125 --> 01:05:57.708
...we take it as it comes.

01:05:57.791 --> 01:05:59.958
[dramatic music playing]

01:06:09.458 --> 01:06:11.458
[chicken clucking]

01:06:13.375 --> 01:06:17.125
[♪ Sheldon Allman:
"Crawl Out through the Fallout"]

01:06:17.208 --> 01:06:20.333
♪ Crawl out through the fallout, baby ♪

01:06:20.416 --> 01:06:22.875
♪ When they drop that bomb ♪

01:06:23.916 --> 01:06:26.291
♪ Crawl out through the fallout ♪

01:06:26.375 --> 01:06:30.375
♪ With the greatest of aplomb ♪

01:06:30.458 --> 01:06:33.583
♪ When your white count's getting higher ♪

01:06:33.666 --> 01:06:36.000
♪ Hurry, don't delay ♪

01:06:36.083 --> 01:06:39.166
♪ I'll hold you close and kiss those ♪

01:06:39.250 --> 01:06:43.208
♪ Radiation burns away ♪

01:06:43.291 --> 01:06:46.333
♪ Crawl out through the fallout, baby ♪

01:06:46.416 --> 01:06:49.125
♪ To my loving arms ♪

01:06:49.208 --> 01:06:56.083
♪ Through the rain of strontium-90 ♪

01:06:56.166 --> 01:06:59.250
♪ Think about your hero ♪

01:06:59.333 --> 01:07:01.708
♪ When you're at ground zero ♪

01:07:01.791 --> 01:07:07.500
♪ And crawl out through the fallout
back to me ♪

01:07:09.875 --> 01:07:14.958
♪ Why don't you crawl out
through the fallout back to me? ♪

01:07:16.083 --> 01:07:22.416
♪ Why don't you crawl out through
the fallout back to me? ♪

01:07:22.500 --> 01:07:28.833
♪ Why don't you crawl out through
the fallout back to... ♪

01:07:28.916 --> 01:07:31.916
♪ Me? ♪♪

01:07:40.083 --> 01:07:42.125
[lighter flicks]

01:07:44.375 --> 01:07:47.041
Oh... hello there.

01:07:47.125 --> 01:07:49.500
Now, how about we turn on some lights?

01:07:51.083 --> 01:07:53.833
[jarring music playing]

01:07:57.125 --> 01:07:58.750
[Wilzig] You need to go home.

01:07:59.791 --> 01:08:02.125
Vault dwellers are
an endangered species here.

01:08:02.208 --> 01:08:04.791
I'm not going back without my dad.

01:08:07.166 --> 01:08:11.416
[Betty] You could have destroyed
the last vestiges of civilization.

01:08:13.083 --> 01:08:15.125
[Dervin] What are you looking at?

01:08:15.208 --> 01:08:16.750
[Norm] A murderer in a cage?

01:08:16.832 --> 01:08:19.457
[Dervin] I don't know what
the people of Vault 32 were up to,

01:08:19.500 --> 01:08:22.750
but it was anything but innocent.

01:08:25.707 --> 01:08:28.082
[Lucy] What happened up here?

01:08:29.082 --> 01:08:31.000
[Maximus] I think everybody wants
to save the world.

01:08:31.082 --> 01:08:33.082
They just disagree on how.

01:08:33.166 --> 01:08:35.457
[Lucy] I wonder if anyone survived.

01:08:37.041 --> 01:08:38.666
[Roger] How long since you first started

01:08:38.750 --> 01:08:39.625
wastelanding?

01:08:39.707 --> 01:08:41.832
A long time.

01:08:41.916 --> 01:08:42.750
[snarls]

01:08:46.125 --> 01:08:47.332
[Lucy] What are you?

01:08:49.291 --> 01:08:51.125
[Ghoul] Oh, I'm you, sweetie.

01:08:52.166 --> 01:08:54.666
Just give it a little time.

01:08:55.541 --> 01:08:56.500
Welcome.

01:08:56.582 --> 01:08:57.666
What the fudge?

01:08:57.750 --> 01:08:59.457
[Sebastian] Forget Hollywood.

01:08:59.541 --> 01:09:01.082
You're a product, I'm a product.

01:09:02.332 --> 01:09:03.625
The end of the world

01:09:03.707 --> 01:09:04.832
is a product.

01:09:04.916 --> 01:09:08.457
[Charles] Vault-Tec is a trillion-dollar
company that owns half of everything.

01:09:08.541 --> 01:09:10.707
[Cooper] I guess everything's
a conspiracy, right?

01:09:11.957 --> 01:09:13.875
[Charles] Unless the people do
something about it.

01:09:17.791 --> 01:09:20.166
[Ghoul] Ain't much stays clean
up here, Vaultie.

01:09:24.457 --> 01:09:25.791
You'll see.

01:09:26.707 --> 01:09:28.957
-[roars]
-[screams]

01:09:39.832 --> 01:09:42.207
[Ghoul] You look out at this wasteland...

01:09:43.207 --> 01:09:45.375
...looks like chaos.

01:09:47.582 --> 01:09:50.000
But there's always somebody
behind the wheel.

01:09:50.082 --> 01:09:52.082
♪ ♪

01:09:57.500 --> 01:09:59.708
[atmospheric music playing]

01:10:28.000 --> 01:10:30.458
♪ ♪

01:11:00.500 --> 01:11:02.958
♪ ♪
